  "prompt": "What is Roadrunner Technical Support?",
  "response": "Roadrunner Technical Support typically refers to customer service and technical assistance for users of the Roadrunner internet service, which was originally offered by Time Warner Cable before it was merged into Spectrum. This support may help users troubleshoot issues related to internet connectivity, email services, and other related technical problems.\n\nServices offered under Roadrunner Technical Support may include:\n\n1. **Internet Connectivity Issues**: Assistance with troubleshooting connectivity problems, slow speeds, and outages.\n2. **Email Support**: Help with setting up, accessing, and troubleshooting Roadrunner email accounts.\n3. **Hardware Support**: Assistance with modems, routers, and other related hardware.\n4. **Account Management**: Help with account settings, billing inquiries, and password resets.\n5. **Installation and Setup**: Guidance on setting up internet services and configuring devices.\n\nSince the name \"Roadrunner\" is less common after Spectrum's acquisition of Time Warner Cable, users might find support under the Spectrum brand instead. If you're looking for support, contacting Spectrum customer service directly would be the best course of action.",
